This paper is about stochastic optimization algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning. The use of non-uniform sampling to reduce variance is a common technique in this field. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses theoretical results related to the multi-armed bandit framework, which suggests cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as another possible category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization algorithms, which could be related to cs.IT (Information Theory).
